==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|striven||to strive}} from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|estriver||to compete, quarrel}} from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|estrif||quarrel, dispute}}, alteration (influenced by {{etyl|gem|en}} forms related to {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*strīban||to strive}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*strībaną}}, {{m|gem-pro|*stribjaną}}, {{m|gem-pro|*stribōną}}, compare {{cog|dum|streven||to strive}}, {{cog|de|streben||to strive}}) of {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|estrit||}}, from {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*strīd||quarrel, dispute}} from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*strīdō||combat, strife}}. Akin to {{cog|goh|strīt||quarrel}} ({{cog|de|Streit||}}), {{cog|goh|strītan||to fight}}, {{cog|non|stríð||strife, contention}}. More at [[stride]].

